Annotations, a form of metadata, provide data about a program that is not part of the program itself. Annotation
have no direct effect on the operation of the code they annotate
Annotation have a number of uses, among them;
- information for the compiler- Annotations can be used by the compiler to detect errors or suppress warnings.
-compile-time and developement-time processing - Software tools can process annotation information to generate code, XML files and so forth
-Runtime processing- Some annotations are available to be examined at runtime